  <channel>
    <title>Re: Power Leveling a Pally</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=238936</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;i just did a cleric with a druid 46 druid.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Do kurns until about 15 or so.&amp;nbsp; PC weaker area till about 23.&amp;nbsp; Head to sol A till it slows down (think it was 30 something).&amp;nbsp; Head to gulf of gunthak beach until about mid 40s.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Kurns is obvious.&amp;nbsp; pull trains. let mobs&amp;nbsp;pound to death on DS.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;PC i started the normal areas but found the DS worked better in the weaker water areas north of the normal areas you hunt.&amp;nbsp; Lots of low con blues up that area and i would just DS me and the druid and pull trains.&amp;nbsp; 5 or 6 mobs at a time pounding themselves to death on the DS.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Because of the way DS works on powerleveling a plate class twink i found just pulling completely ridicolous trains and then healing the twink worked better with lower cons in some situations.&amp;nbsp; This was one.&amp;nbsp; Plus up north of the normal area i was all alone and had unfettered access to all the mobs i wanted.&amp;nbsp; It turns out there are areas of level 16ish(?)&amp;nbsp;mobs in PC that nobody ever touches!&amp;nbsp; Hordes and hordes of mobs to pull and nobody ever goes there cause its just better to do the level 18+ mobs unless your pulling trains unto a damage shield =)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;One thing a cleric has that a paladin doesnt is an AE spell so that i could get the 1pt of damage needed to get exp.&amp;nbsp; So youll have to work a little harder to get the 1pt of damage in.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Sol A is great while they were yellow+.&amp;nbsp; I think that will be more valuable as a hot spot then chasing undead.&amp;nbsp; The DS from your druid will work better that way.&amp;nbsp; Again same strat.&amp;nbsp; Pull trains keep twink alive until DS kills the train.&amp;nbsp; Do some minor damage with twink.&amp;nbsp; Cleric actually saved my 46 druids butt here a couple times on overpulls but alas you shouldnt have that problem with a 61 druid.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The beach in the gulf of gunthak is &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) low hp&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) undead&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) a hotspot&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So I stayed there all the way until 46!&amp;nbsp; Which was about 2 levels to long for that beach but i wanted to push to 46 where my main could take over the leveling of the cleric.&amp;nbsp; The reason it worked so well was the cleric could dps undead so much better then live mobs.&amp;nbsp; You might want to leave that beach sooner but in the low 30s it should serve you nice.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;After 46 I just grouped the cleric with a 70 rogue and went to town exping in hotspots.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;All and all i wouldnt chase undead at the start.&amp;nbsp; Your chasing low hp hotspot zones where you can pull trains onto the DS and kill things that way.&amp;nbsp; Thats far more efficient then chasing undead.&amp;nbsp; The kinds of buffs your casting are skins, heals, regens and damage shields.&amp;nbsp; The paladin is set up to tank.&amp;nbsp; Your focus is on pulling the most that you can still heal the paladin (or your druid)&amp;nbsp;fast enough to keep him alive.&amp;nbsp; Thats how your going to cruise to 50 the fastest.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Im not sure i would skip out on hotspots in the 50s just to chase undead either.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
