    <item>
      <title>Re: Power Leveling a Pally</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=239103#M239103</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
beefhouse wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I started a Pally last night and think I'm going to try and power level him up. All my other alts have had the slow grind. I'd take them out and do all the newbie quests. For a change I'm going to twink this toon a bit and try to get him some levels a little faster. I was going to work on 1Hs and 2Hs and skip the 1Hb and 2Hb. At least for now. I'll 2box this toon with my 61 Druid for awhile then use another alt later. Any advice since I've never power leveled a toon before?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Get a massive dragonclaw shard as a weapon. It's bazaar buyable, no recommended level, and the ratio will make up for the lack of a proc. Fill all his slots with the best gear you can, get him a temperance, hti him with thorns and regen, and start pulling stuff. Just make sure you hit each one at least once, and the druid does no damage, so you get credit for the kills.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I would not really worry about weapons skills (other than 1hs)&amp;nbsp;until 40ish. From 40-50 exp slows down a bit, and all skill caps stay at 200 for 10 levels, so it's a good time to catch the skills up.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
