      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Well this weekend was a blast! One of the best weekends yet. I did the tutorial to 10, one quick stop to do a newbie quest with just the pally to gauge his skills. I've done that quest with every toon I've created. Went to Kurn's Tower till 15. Alternated PC and Unrest till 25 then when to Iceclad Ocean. At lvl 30 I shed the Gloomingdeep armor and got what I could in the Bazaar for 7k. Not great but upgrade again in another 15 - 20 lvl's. All skills are improving nicely, except bash. No matter what I do it doesn't seem to move up. What's the secret in getting the bash skill up?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I'm lvl 32 now and I'll probably stay in Iceclad till they turn Dk Blue, just a few are now. I've been picking on Frosted Ice Giants, not sure what lvl they are. I bow pull the mob and start whacking it, switch to Druid and snare, heal and buff when necessary. I buy spells 10 lvl's at a time. So there in no down time at all. I never really knew how powerful the Druid DS was till I did this. You'll never see my Druid without this. The Pally is progressing nicely and can't wait to get him into his forties so I can 2 box with the Druid and they both can get exp.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
